  "notes": "Ido (1907; reformed Esperanto). Uses the plain 26-letter Latin alphabet with no diacritics: ⟨c⟩ = /ts/, ⟨ch⟩ = /tʃ/, ⟨sh⟩ = /ʃ/, ⟨j⟩ = /ʒ/ (~/dʒ/), ⟨qu⟩ = /kw/ (~/kv/), ⟨x⟩ = /ks/ (~/ɡz/), ⟨y⟩ = /j/, ⟨w⟩ = /w/. Stress is on the penultimate syllable, except verb infinitives, which are stressed on the final syllable.",
